5:
Well, here we are, on our way to
investigate a dragon lair. Hopefully,
they're just friendly new neighbors...
9:
With the amount of crazy dragons
running around lately, the Guild
doesn't seem to think so...
41:
Vexing, revolting... Pitiful slaves to
fate.
57:
Anbach, the Frigid Fang. You know
who I am, don't you?
61:
...Champions, our various worlds...
They have nothing to do with me
now. We have nothing to talk about.
64:
Or do you intend on making me
submit to the natural order once
more? Is your small stature even
capable of such a feat?
69:
No... I follow that destiny no longer. I
only—
78:
I wasn't here to help you. I only
came to release these wretched
souls from their fate.
83:
You know, we heard a bunch of
dragons were living together in the
area. You wouldn't happen to know
anything about that, would you?
87:
No. I'm not interested in matters that
don't concern me.
89:
I already have enough to deal with.
Leave me be—
93:
Heeey! Wait up, Anbach! I've been
looking for you!
100:
Oh, I didn't know you guys were
friends with each other!
106:
...So you've been letting the dragons
stay here with you.
110:
No. These children decided to live
here without my permission.
115:
This goes beyond simply just
feeding a few lost dragons, like you
claimed to be doing earlier...
119:
But that's simply all I did. They're the
ones who decided to follow me
home and take up residence.
124:
Anbach's super nice, so she looks
after everyone. Keeps picking up
strays to bring home too.
128:
That's actually how I ended up here!
One quick chat later, and she
started taking care of me!
141:
...They're here for the food and the
toys, honestly.
150:
...Enough. You have discovered the
dragon's lair. What will you do now?
Slaughter them all?
153:
What? Aren't dragons perceived as
a threat to you two-legged mortals?
157:
We're only here to investigate.
Besides, none of these guys look like
the rampaging dragons we're
searching for.
161:
Were the dragons you fought earlier
previous residents of this place?
166:
No. If that were the case, I would
have ended them before they left.
169:
Those children were swallowed by
the wrath of the serpents.
172:
Robbed of reason, fallen dragons
like them seek to return to the origin.
177:
Origin? Is there something you're not
telling us?
181:
...No, I have no more to say on this
matter.
184:
As you can see, there are no
rampaging dragons among us. If
you're done, then leave.
192:
I live in the present moment, the
way I wish to. I have no interest in
involving myself in your matters.
195:
Do whatever you like with those
dragons. There's no saving—
204: Then we will search for a cure.
208:
...Were you listening to me? Those
dragons are too far gone.
212:
You said we could do whatever we
liked. So we will.
221:
I am of the same mind. I don't want
these children to suffer the same
fate.
224:
If your heart is as kind as I believe it
to be... We shall meet again in the
future.
229:
You know about Starview Village,
right?
232:
Stop by to hang out whenever you
feel like. I can cook up a meal for
you, if you're interested.
236:
We've got the seal of approval from
other dragons, including ancient
ones. I'm sure you'll find it to your
liking as well.
243:
I shall not submit once more to the
bonds of fate.
249:
You sure didn't waste time coming
here, huh?
253:
The decision was made of my own
volition. I'm allowed to do what I
wish.
256:
Don't get the wrong idea. I'm here
because I'm curious about your
cooking—not to offer my aid.
269:
I dislike noise, but... it's better than
being bored, I suppose.
